bib_record.title: A study of the 29,30Si(a,d)31,32P and the 29,30Si(d,a)27,28Al reactions.

free_txt: A 25 MeV beam of alpha particles and a 12.3
MeV tensor polarised deuteron beam from the University
of Birmingham Radial Ridge cyclotron was used.
Four telescopes of delta E x E
solid state detectors were placed 5 degr apart on
each of two arms in the scattering chamber. The
delta E x E arrangement, consisting of a surface
barrier passing detector and a lithium drifted silicon
stopping detector, was used for particle identification
in conjunction with an analogue multiplier.

systematic. Uncertainties in the integrator counts and
detector  angles and solid angles are neligible.
